Date: Wed, 6 Aug 2008 07:49:33 -0400
From: Philip Tierno <philip.tierno@nyumc.org>


Re: ProMED-mail Anthrax, human, 2001 - USA (03) 20080805.2406
-------------------------------------------------------------
The report overlooks some important bits of incriminating evidence
and that is an analysis of the spores used showed that they were
unique and of 2 types:
1. the Ames strain from USAMRIID [United States Army Medical Research
Institute for Infectious Diseases]
and
2. spores from Dunlap (Utah) Army Proving Ground

The spores contained in the letters were genotyped by a very
sophisticated high-resolution device by Ibis Bioscience Lab in
Carlsbad, California. This technology has only recently been made available.

Ivins admitted to the FBI during their follow-up investigation in
2002 that he used the same 2 spore types for his vaccine challenge.
He named them as the Ames and Dunlop samples. These same 2 spore
types were indeed found in Ivins's lab and on his glassware thusly
confirming his statement and confirming their unique identity with
the bioterrorist envelopes.

The "milling" was done by the post office roller machines so that the
last letter that had the longest post office route, therefore being
milled most, was the best "weaponized" sample. The others were less
"milled" so to speak. One could start out with a simple lyophilized
sample and after the post office machines processed the envelopes,
they were near military grade. That weaponization was likely
unintended, incidental, and unplanned by the perp.

--
Philip M Tierno, Jr, PhD
